        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>JOSEPH BLUMENTHAL&#44;<lb/>
                <emph rend="italics">President&#44;</emph><lb/>
                151 EAST 73D STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>Jewish Theological Seminary Association.<lb/></p>
            <p><del>New York</del> Albany Mch 5 1890<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr<lb/></p>
            <p>Your several favors to hand&#45;&#45;<lb/> I am very sorry that you will not be<lb/> able to be with us on Sunday morning of the<lb/> 16th at opening of conventions&#45;&#45;&#40;will you please<lb/> send your report to me as soon as possible&#44;<lb/> so that I can get everything in shape<lb/> &#38; will you pardon me for saying that I<lb/> hope you will severely leave Cincinnati &#38;c<lb/> alone and deal entirely with our own affairs&#45;&#45;<lb/> I am sure you agree with me that silence<lb/> on our part to all their assaults &#38;c&#44; and<lb/> a true adherence to our principles and<lb/> methods is our best course&#45;&#45;we must also<lb/> avoid our reports being too long&#45;&#45;I trust<lb/> Dr Drachman has sent you all and<lb/> full reports&#45;&#45;Happy to hear of Miss Phillips<lb/> generous donation of &#36;200&#45;&#45;I have raised &#36;500&#45;&#45;<lb/> among my Trustees of the Seminary here&#45;&#45;<lb/> So matters are not so very gloomy&#45;&#45;all<lb/> will yet be right&#45;&#45;I will hold the<lb/> convention so that you can participate<lb/></p> 
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>if you get there by 4 oclock&#45;&#45;<lb/> Yours Truly<lb/> Joseph Blumenthal<lb/></p>
            <p>I have several excellent new<lb/> Trustees that have promised to<lb/> come in<lb/></p>
            <p>Try to send me your report by Sunday or<lb/> Monday of this week if possible to<lb/> New York&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
